{
  "texts": [
    "Understand the biases: Large language models learn from the data they are trained on, which can contain societal biases.",
    "Be aware of these biases and take steps to mitigate them by using diverse training data and evaluating the outputs for fairness.",
    "Collaborate and share knowledge: Engage in open dialogue with other researchers and scientists working with language models.",
    "Share experiences, discuss challenges, and collectively work towards best practices for using these models in scientific research.",
    "Maintain transparency: When presenting work that incorporates the use of large language models, disclose the methodology, tools, and limitations."
  ]
}